\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 He enters the second bus:
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Its coolness sedating the skin that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Overlaps his troubled mind.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 His thoughts pull together
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Like the light, cool flow of the air conditioning.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 He feels a little pacified.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 He knows the shadow's inta\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 ngible depth:
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Its vastness having overpowered him these months
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Until he could not reach the logic that told him
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 To find himself outside its barriers.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 As he stares out of the window
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 He wonders why she has left.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 How could she have left without indication
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Whe\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 n he has remained angled toward work
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 So that he and his wife can stay alive?
