\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2                      Earth
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 I use her earth to plant my seed--
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 My limbs twisting around the collective molecules,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Trying to dig in.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Only the obscurity of my body
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Presses so fully that it is neither
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Body nor b\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 ed nor the intersection of both,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 But euphoric traction;
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 And then, planted and repulsed,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Only the seam of backbone minutely faces her,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 That bed of earth.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 With all conscious force
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 I breathe the aloneness that intangibly defines the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Air.  I swallow its ambros\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 ia
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Of depth and ask myself
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Why I ever married the woman.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 There is void.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Then a hollow answer calls my name and says "it was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 time."
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 I realize myself in movement, parting the scene.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 I use what has been planted for the reaping--
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 My suit tucks me into its str\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 ucture of cotton;
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 And soon a building will be again the structure
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Around men of cotton suits, pushing a product.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Lost, I drink my coffee alone on the stoop.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 She had asked to fix me breakfast
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 But I would not let her.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 My miniature is one and black.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 I drink \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 me in when I am not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Pressed by the coffee's steam.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Cars' casketed phantoms of people
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Chasing up and down Dunlavy Street of Houston
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 After something--their whole lives after something--
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Come and go from consciousness like respiration.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 The people plant and re\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 ap.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Who can count all of their
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Insignificant names?--
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Animals that are not created sensible enough
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 To propagate unless lost to frenzy,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Caught in structures without meaning.
