\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2                     Bar-Room Buddies
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 We Mongoled Human experience.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 We pushed it into our mouths
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 As the crisp pretzels of which the shape became salty
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 dust
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 At our tastes: the crispness of life,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 And we Mongoled human experience.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 The tequila, that Sandras o\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 r Cassandras, or whomever
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 it had beeen
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 At the moment of malevolently blessing our heated and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Maddening consumption, was what we left
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Our wives for; and then hardened ourselves on
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 The springless cushions of the sofas of our friends
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Whom we eventually forgot\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2  the names of:
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 The wetness of human experience that we Mongoled,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 And felt the bladed emptiness
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Of stomachs that could not consume food
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 On mornings after.  But the Angels of bar rooms
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 continually
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Appeared before darkened stages where, in front of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 guitars,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 W\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 e played.  They apppeared at various stages to the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 weeks of the years.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 They came, silently whispering themselves off
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 As Sandras or Cassandras;
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Stared up at us for two hours; and disappeared.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 The reappearance of their light enamored us, and we
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 left
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 And foll\hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 owed but found bats that offered
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 No shelter, and often caves we could not fit into
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Or were forbidden from entering.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 We invested our capital
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 In the Silicon Valleys of this great nation.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Third-world bitches, in factories, became sick for our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 chips.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 We held \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 power.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 We bred metals and bought the ownership titles
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Of properties, but could not find a home of the world.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 We married again and brought forth children
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af2\loch\f2 Who were duplicate strangers of ourselves.
